result.execSummary:
The defendant Keath Eugene Fox was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Keath Eugene Fox in court with attorney Robert E Webb.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg  

VETERAN COURT

Based upon the defendant's compliance with Veterans Treatment Initiative Court, court finds the agreement is fulfilled.  Defendant is awarded with a Certificate and a Medallion of completion of Veterans Treatment Initiative.


Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1:

On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, As Party to a Crime,  contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor.

Defendant ordered to serve 2 (TWO) DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 (TWO) days served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

* Balance of Restitution ($987.64) to BMO HARRIS BANK is ordered to be converted FORTHWITH to a Civil Judgment.

Defendant ordered to pay all costs, penalties, surcharges by 11-04-2016 a civil judgment will be entered WITHOUT tax intercept.  Bail on deposit if applicable to be applied.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Order for Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit Form.
